H0.text: Rotation is the term that describes the path the Moon travels around Earth.

H1.text: Day is the term that describes the path the Moon travels around Earth.

H2.text: Orbit is the term that describes the path the Moon travels around Earth.

H3.text: Phase is the term that describes the path the Moon travels around Earth.

A4.text: Known as an orbital revolution, examples include the trajectory of a planet around a star, a natural satellite around a planet, or an artificial satellite around an object or position in space such as a planet, moon, asteroid, or Lagrange point.

A5.text: In celestial mechanics, an orbit is the curved trajectory of an object under the influence of an attracting force.
